Text: Signs of an STD are different between guys and girls. And sometimes, there aren’t any signs at all. Guys SOMETIMES have things like sores, blisters, or pain when they pee but most of the time, they won’t have any symptoms at all. For girls, STD symptoms might look like an itchy vagina, blisters, rashes, nasty discharge (I’m talking funky, yellow, or bloody stuff), or pain when peeing or during sex.

Text: What's it like to get an STD test?
Message JSON: {"userId":"920e0a2a-660e-4a37-a59d-dc35ac0f5cd3","text":"What's it like to get an STD test?"}

Text: STD tests are over 99% accurate and they’re really quick and easy to get done. Usually it involves peeing in a cup, a finger prick, or a vagina swab - and it doesn’t take longer than a few minutes. It’s also super easy to find a place to get tested. If you're worried about it - just get tested ASAP. It's worth it to know!
